# Server Configuration
PORT=3000

# SMTP Configuration for Gmail
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_SECURE=false
SMTP_USER=your-gmail@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-16-char-app-password
SMTP_FROM=noreply@gujwear.live

# Other settings
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
NOTIFY_EMAIL=official@gujwear.live

## Serverless / Vercel / Supabase (Option B)
# If deploying to Vercel as serverless functions, set these environment variables in the Vercel project settings.
# Use a Supabase service role key for server-side writes (keep this secret).
# SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_KEY are required for Option B endpoints under /api
# FRONTEND_URL should be your public frontend URL (e.g. https://www.gujwear.live)
# SUBSCRIPTIONS_TABLE defaults to 'subscriptions' if omitted
# Example:
# SUPABASE_URL=https://xyzcompany.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
# FRONTEND_URL=https://www.gujwear.live
# SUBSCRIPTIONS_TABLE=subscriptions

## Vercel-specific notes
# - Set variables in Vercel Dashboard > Project > Settings > Environment Variables
# - Use the Production environment for live keys
# - If you want serverless to send real emails, also set SMTP_* and NOTIFY_EMAIL

